  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Concrete mix truck driver",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Provide\ncustomer service by safely and efficiently transporting the goods from batching\nplant to customer’s site</p><p>· Unloading\nthe goods at the designated job sites within time frame</p><p>· To\nmaintain and keep assigned trucks clean at all times</p><p>· To ensure\nthat the mixer drums are free of hardened concrete at all times</p><p>· To carry\nout visual checks on concrete slumps and follow procedures for the same</p><p>· To carry\nout truck maintenance according to the truck maintenance checklist at the\nplanned interval</p><p>· To deliver\nDo's to the customer upon delivery of goods and ensure that Do's are signed and\nreturned to the plant</p><p>· To carry\nout any other tasks as per instructed</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· High\nschool, diploma or GED.</p><p>· Proven\ndriving experience in the Logistics Department as a concrete Truck Driver with\nat least 3 years Experience .</p><p>· Verified\nCommercial Driver License (CDL) will be preferred.</p><p>·\nProfessional CDL training will be preferred.</p><p>· Must pass\nthe drug and alcohol test.</p><p>· A clean\ndriving record will be preferred.</p><p>· Strong\nworking knowledge of using the GPS and ability to plan routes accordingly.</p><p>· Solid\nunderstanding of truck driving rules and regulations.</p><p>· Ability to\nwork for long working hours and Night Shifts .</p><p>· Ability to\ntransport goods in all types of commercial vehicles, for example, Concrete\nMixer truck etc.<br />· Quick\ndecision-making skills.</p><p>·\nHardworking and trustworthy individual.</p><p>· Good time\nmanagement skills.</p>",
